$x_{1}$ is a tile/cake [shape/form] of material $x_{2}$, shape $x_{3}$, thickness $x_{4}$.
column7: A tile is a 3-dimensional object, relatively uniform and significant in the 3rd dimension, but thin enough that its shape in the the other two dimensions is a significant feature; 'city block' is conceptually a tile; polygon (= {taplytai} or {kardytai} - shaped like an approximately-2-dimensional block, {lijyclupa} - a loop composed of lines).  (cf. {bliku}, {kubli}, {matci}; {karda}, for which the 3rd dimension is insignificant, {bliku}, {kurfa}, {matci}, {plita}, {tarmi})

column2: $x_{1}$ is an embryo/zygote/fetus/fertilized egg with mother $x_{2}$, and father $x_{3}$.
$x_{1}$ is a star/sun with stellar properties $x_{2}$.
$x_{1}$ is a quantity of/contains/is made of tar/asphalt from source $x_{2}$.
$x_{1}$ [ideal] is the conceptual shape/form of object/abstraction/manifestation $x_{2}$ (object/abstract).
column7: Also pattern; $x_1$ is the mathematical or theoretical ideal form, while $x_2$ is an object/event manifesting that form; e.g. circular/circle-shaped (= {cukseltai}) vs. circle (={cuktai}, while {cukla} alone is ambiguous); model (= {ci'ersaptai}, {saptai}, {ci'ersmitai}, {smitai}).  See alse {nejni}, te {marji} for physical shape, {tapla}, {bliku}, {kubli}, {kurfa}, {cukla}, {mapti}, {morna}, {sarlu}.

column2: $x_{1}$ behaves/conducts oneself as/in-manner $x_{2}$ (event/property) under conditions $x_{3}$.
$x_{1}$ thirsts for $x_{2}$; $x_{1}$ needs/wants drink/fluid/lubrication $x_{2}$.
$x_{1}$ is tired/fatigued by effort/situation $x_{2}$ (event); $x_{1}$ needs/wants rest.
$x_{1}$ is a/the breast/mammary/teat [body-part] of $x_{2}$; [metaphor: projection providing liquid].
$x_{1}$ talks/speaks to $x_{2}$ about subject $x_{3}$ in language $x_{4}$.
column7: Not limited to vocal speech, but this is implied by the $x_4$ without context of some other medium of conversation (use {cusku}, {casnu}, {skicu}, {ciksi} for weaker implication of vocal communication); converse/discuss/chat (= {simta'a}, {simsku}, {vricysimta'a} for a conversation not clearly delimited by subject).  See also {bacru}, {cusku} for actual expression, {casnu}, {darlu}, {skicu}, {ciksi}, {bangu}.

column2: $x_{1}$ is dress/a garment/clothing for wearing by $x_{2}$ (gender/species/body part) serving purpose $x_{3}$.
column7: Also: $x_2$ can wear/is wearing $x_1$; refers to something intended for use as a garment, not merely something that happens to be worn at some time (which need not be true for dasni).  See also {creka}, {cutci}, {daski}, {dasni}, {gluta}, {kosta}, {mapku}, {palku}, {pastu}, {skaci}, {smoka}, {lunbe}.

column2: $x_{1}$ is a custom/habit/[ritual/rut] of $x_{2}$ under conditions $x_{3}$.
column7: Also: $x_1$ is customary/usual/the practice.  See also {fadni}, {kampu}, {lakne}, {jinzi}, {ckaji}, {cnano}, {tarti}, {ritli}, {javni}, {zekri}.

column2: $x_{1}$ is a town/city of metropolitan area $x_{2}$, in political unit $x_{3}$, serving hinterland/region $x_{4}$.
$x_{1}$ is a station/node of/in/on transport/communication/distribution system/network $x_{2}$.
column7: $x_2$ may be represented by massed vehicles of system.  See also {dargu}, {litru}, {pluta}, {trene}, {ciste}, ve {mrilu}, {tivni}, {cradi}, ve {benji}, {fonxa}, {dikca}, {fatri}.

column2: $x_{1}$ is made of/contains/is a quantity of tea brewed from leaves $x_{2}$.
$x_{1}$ stretches/extends to range $x_{2}$ [interval/extent] in dimension $x_{3}$ from relaxed range $x_{4}$.
discursive: \n{ta'u} - expanding the tanru\n{ta'unai} - making a tanru.
2-word letteral/shift: change case for next letteral only.
$x_1$ is the way or manner in which activity/event $x_2$ is done/happens
column7: Lojban has always been lacking a gismu for "x1 is the manner of event x2" or similar. Later, {tai} started to be used for it, and then, since a BAI needs a brivla (usually a gismu) to be based on, they invented tamsmi. So {tasmi} is a true brivla for {tai}, the BAI of {tasmi}. Cf. {tai}, {tamsmi}

column2: $x_1$ is a taste of $x_2$
$x_1$ (object) has charge $x_2$ (number) in units $x_3$ for interaction/of type $x_4$ and in/by/using convention $x_5$
column7: Generic type of charge; individual charges tend to be scalars. For electromagnetism, the meaning of a "positive charge" is either the signum of the charge of an electron for electricity or the signum of the charge of a south magnet for magnetism. Includes mass (gravitation charge ({gavytcaxe}) if it is being treated as such; x2 default: {ma'u}), electric charge ({dicmytcaxe}), (strong) isospin, weak isospin, color charge (Quantum Chromodynamics; {tsabytcaxe}), intrinsic spin/Dirac-Pauli charge, most quantum numbers (lepton number, baryon number), etc. See also: {majga}, {dikca}, {eldicka'u}, {kuardicka'u}, {paulcna}, {plankexu}, {grake}.

column2: $x_1$ are blinds for covering $x_2$, made of material $x_3$
$k_2$ is a board game played by $k_1$ on board $t_1$.
column7: Can be used metaphorically for games played on a digital board. For a broader word that includes any games played on a physical/digital table, see {jbuselkei}.

column2: $x_1$ is a tablet computer for purpose $x_2$
$x_{1}$ is a board-chair with board material $x_{2}$.
$x_1$ stumbles/trips over $x_2$ and falls/drops to/onto $x_3$
$si_1$ is a track of $st_1$ treading on surface $st_2$ using limb $st_3$
$x_1$=$s_1$=$d_1$ tap-dances to accompaniment/music/rhythm $x_2$=$d_2$.
$g_1$ is $g_2$ pace/paces (length unit).
$b_1$ is a globular cluster consisting of stars with properties $t_2$.
$x_1$ is an asterisk (* character)
$a_1$ is a/the fetal position of body $a_2$ characterized by property/(set of) properties $a_3$ (ka).
$x_1$ is a placental mammal of species $x_2$.
column7: From {tarbykanrango} {mabru}. Default: an animal belonging to infraclass Placentalia.

column2: $x_1$ is a placenta supporting fetus $x_2$ in/of mother's body $x_3$.
$s_1$ is the/a umbilical cord connecting $t_1$=$x_2$ to mother $t_2$=$x_3$.
$s_1$=$t_1$ is a zygote with mother $t_2$, and father $t_3$.
$v_1$ is pregnant with embryo/zygote/fetus/fertilized egg $v_2$=$t_1$ with mother $t_2$ (default x1), and father $t_3$.
column7: The child-bearer x1 isn't necessarily the same as the egg donator x3.

column2: $v_1$ performs abortion/induces delivery of embryo/zygote/fetus/fertilized egg $t_1$=$v_2$ on $t_2$=$v_3$.  (The survival/death of $t_1$=$v_2$ is not implied.)
$x_1$=$c_1$ is a star chart of/about $x_2$=$c_2$ showing formation/data-points $x_3$=$c_3$
$c_1$ is a solar/stellar system based on star(s) $t_1$ (default is the Solar System) with stellar properties $t_2$ with components $c_3$ displaying $c_4$ (ka).
$x_1$=$g_1$ is a star cluster showing common property (ka) $x_2$=$g_2$ due to set $x_3$=$g_3$ linked by relations $x_4$=$g_4$
column7: from {tarci}+{girzu} can either indicate an open cluster, a globular cluster or a galaxy.

column2: $x_1$ is stellar astronomy based on methodology $x_2$.
$l_1$ is an asphalt lake / a tar lake.
$p_1$ tars or puts tar $p_2$=$t_1$ on $p_3$.
$s_1$ is a/the galaxy (default is the Milky Way)
column7: Cf. {tarci}, {so'imei}, {sostartai}, {tarboi}, {tarci'e}, "{galki}" (which is a gismu and does not reference stars specifically).

column2: $tarm_1$ tartai $tarc_2$.
$c_1$ is a/the mammary gland secreting milk $c_2$, of breast $t_1$.
$x_1$=$d_2$ is a mastodon of species $x_2$
column7: The mastodon's English name (and former genus name) comes from "breast-tooth" due to the unusual shape of its molars.  They are not in the same family as elephants or mammoths. This is also {xantrmamutu}.

column2: $t_1$=$j_1$ a nipple/teat (mammary papilla) of $t_2$.
$tax_1$ is a bra with purpose $tax_2$.
